Cell C to Compensate Blackberry Users for Service Disruption

-- B y   H i l t o n   S h o n e
-- 
2011-10-13T14:34:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/cell-c-to-compensate-blackberry-users-for-service-disruption.html
Cell C Pty Ltd said today it’s
deducting 10 rand from the bill of users of the Blackberry
Internet/Enterprise Service for the month of October after the
disruption in  Research in Motion Ltd (RIM) ’s service this week.  Users will also get 10 free mobile-phone text messages for
the time they could not use Blackberry Messenger, the mobile
phone company said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Hilton Shone at 
 hshone@bloomberg.net  